フェイの倉庫について
It's a warehouse owned by a person named Fei.
Without the key to Fei's warehouse, you can't enter.
If you can get inside...
情報選択
ピエルについて
Pier is a strange brigade of 15 people wearing clown masks.

It seems they enjoy hiding in various places as if playing hide and
seek.

If you find them, they'll smile brightly and then disappear again, but
finding all 15 might bring you some good fortune.
情報選択
小さなコインについて
It's about a special small coin made by a certain person.
It seems only 30 were made, but I don't know much more than that.

If you can find the coin, you should look for a certain woman in the
Dinos district.
She seems willing to trade it for something rare.
情報選択
敵の弱点について
Every formidable enemy has a weakness.

Broadly speaking, enemies can be classified as weak to physical
attacks or weak to magical attacks.

For example, the Meat Massa Shop attacker, Eeto-Daagu, was strong
against physical attacks but weak to magical attacks.

It's important to judge whether physical or magical attacks are
effective based on appearance, but actually attacking is the best way
to determine it.

Furthermore, enemies can be classified as weak to fire, weak to
lightning, weak to wind, or weak to holy attacks.

For instance, the Meat Massa Shop attacker, Eeto-Daagu, was weak to
fire attributes.

If it's a weakness attribute, attacks will succeed with 120% power, so
it's also trial and error to find out which attribute they're weak
against.

Last but not least, there are rare enemies that launch dark attribute
attacks. That's an attribute you can't handle.
情報選択
バフとデバフについて

A buff state refers to a condition where beneficial effects are
applied to oneself.

For example, \i[34] indicates a state where attack power is increased
by 15%, and \i[42] indicates a state where attack power is increased
by 30%.

Conversely, a debuff state refers to a condition where detrimental
effects are applied to oneself.

For example, \i[50] indicates a state where attack power is decreased
by 15%, and \i[58] indicates a state where attack power is decreased
by 30%.

The number of turns for which buffs and debuffs are effective is
predetermined, so paying attention during battle can give you an
advantage.

As an application, if you're in a state where your attack power is
reduced by 15% with \i[50], you can offset the debuff by increasing
your attack power by 15% with \i[34].
情報選択

小さなコインについて
It's about a special small coin made by a certain person.
It seems only 30 were made, but I don't know much more than that.

If you can find the coin, you should look for a certain woman in the
Dinos district.
She's said to exchange it for something rare.
情報選択
敵の弱点について
Every formidable enemy has a weakness.

Broadly speaking, enemies can be classified as weak to physical
attacks or weak to magical attacks.

For example, the Meat Massa that attacked the butcher shop was strong
against physical attacks but weak to magical attacks.

It's important to judge whether physical or magical attacks are
effective based on appearance, but the best way is to actually attack
and decide.

Furthermore, if we classify more specifically, there are enemies weak
to fire, weak to lightning, weak to wind, and weak to holy attacks.

For instance, the Meat Massa that attacked the butcher shop was weak
to fire attributes.

If it's a weakness attribute, attacks will be successful with 120%
power, so it's also trial and error to find out which attribute
they're weak against.

Last but not least, there are very rare enemies that launch dark
attribute attacks. This is an attribute you cannot handle.
情報選択
バフとデバフについて

A buff state refers to a condition where beneficial effects are
applied to oneself.

For example, \i[34] indicates a state where attack power is increased
by 15%, and \i[42] indicates a state where attack power is increased
by 30%.

Conversely, a debuff state refers to a condition where detrimental
effects are applied to oneself.

For example, \i[50] indicates a state where attack power is decreased
by 15%, and \i[58] indicates a state where attack power is decreased
by 30%.

The number of turns for which buffs and debuffs are effective is
predetermined, so pay attention and fight accordingly to gain an
advantage in battle.

As an application, if you're in a state with \i[50] attack power
decreased by 15% and you use \i[34] to increase attack power by 15%,
you can offset the debuff.
